y=c+ x*m

y= model1

c= intercept a[1] first value of the vector a m= slope a[2] second value of vector a

what output does model function give ? what are its inputs ?

model1 <- function(a, data) {
  a[1] + data$x * a[2]
}

vec_a=c(11, 2.5)
model1(vec_a, sim1)
##  [1] 13.5 13.5 13.5 16.0 16.0 16.0 18.5 18.5 18.5 21.0 21.0 21.0 23.5 23.5 23.5
## [16] 26.0 26.0 26.0 28.5 28.5 28.5 31.0 31.0 31.0 33.5 33.5 33.5 36.0 36.0 36.0

What are the inputs for measure distance function ? what is its output ?

measure_distance <- function(mod, data) {
  
  prediction=model1(mod, data)
  diff <- data$y - prediction
  sqrt(mean(diff ^ 2))
}
measure_distance(c(10, .9), sim1)
## [1] 3.971912

what does mutate do ? what does purr::map2_bl do ? what are the columns in new models tibble/dataframe ?

sim1_dist <- function(a1, a2) {
  measure_distance(c(a1, a2), sim1)
}

models <- models %>% 
  mutate(dist = purrr::map2_dbl(a1, a2, sim1_dist))

models

what does rank function do? what does filter do ?

filter(models, rank(dist) <= 10)

Please interprete the following chart.

ggplot(sim1, aes(x, y)) + 
  geom_point(size = 2, colour = "grey30") + 
  geom_abline(
    aes(intercept = a1, slope = a2, colour = -dist), 
    data = filter(models, rank(dist) <= 10)
  )
